OL,3,CProtest laws based on 'kneejerk public
OL,4,Copinion', says think tank
OL,6,FPolly Curtis, chief executive of
OL,7,FDemos, said: "Too often, politicians
OL,8,Fhave relied on knee-jerk public
OL,9,Fopinion, itself based on limited
OL,10,Fknowledge of the protest landscape.
OL,12,F"However, by providing people with
OL,13,Fbalanced information and exposing them
OL,14,Fto different viewpoints, it's clear
OL,15,Fthat people's views are far more
OL,16,Fnuanced and there is more consensus
OL,17,Fthan recent clampdowns account for.
OL,19,F"The public recognises protest as a
OL,20,Ffundamental right, and strongly
OL,21,Fbelieves it should be protected."
